2026-05-07 | Check if One Tree is Subtree of Another

Question
Return true if S is a subtree of T.
	Approach
1.	Create helper function isSame():
		check whether two trees are identical  
2.	For every node in T:
		check:
			is subtree rooted here identical to S?  
3.	If yes → return true  
4.	Otherwise recursively search:
		left subtree  
		right subtree  
	Time Complexity
	O(N × M) worst case
	Space Complexity
	O(height of tree)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isSame(Node* a, Node* b){
        if(a == NULL && b == NULL)
            return true;
        if(a == NULL || b == NULL)
            return false;
        return (a->data == b->data) &&
               isSame(a->left, b->left) &&
               isSame(a->right, b->right);
    }
    bool isSubTree(Node* root1, Node* root2) {
        if(root2 == NULL) return true;
        if(root1 == NULL) return false;
        if(isSame(root1, root2))
            return true;
        return isSubTree(root1->left, root2) ||
               isSubTree(root1->right, root2);
    }
};
	Key Insight
The problem breaks into two recursive tasks:
1.	Find candidate node in T  
2.	Check if both trees are identical from that node  
This recursive decomposition makes the solution simple and clean.
